                <li>If intra-state: CGST ≈ ₹300, SGST ≈ ₹300</li>
              </ul>

              <h2>Frequently asked questions about GST calculation in India</h2>

              <h3>Is GST calculated on MRP or transaction value?</h3>
              <p>
                Legally, GST is levied on the
                <strong>transaction value</strong> (price actually paid or
                payable), which may be equal to or lower than the printed MRP.
                Discounts shown on the invoice before tax reduce the taxable
                value; post-supply discounts may be adjusted subject to
                conditions.
              </p>

              <h3>
                How do I calculate GST for a mixed supply with different rates?
              </h3>
              <p>
                If your invoice contains items with different GST rates (e.g. 5%
                and 18%), calculate GST
                <strong>item-wise</strong>:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  Compute GST for each line item using its applicable rate.
                </li>
                <li>
                  Sum up the base values and tax amounts to get the invoice
                  totals.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                You can run the calculator multiple times for each rate, or use
                it as a quick check for individual lines.
              </p>

              <h3>
                Does this calculator handle cess (e.g. compensation cess)?
              </h3>
              <p>
                This tool focuses on <strong>GST rate only</strong> (CGST, SGST,
                IGST). If a particular good attracts an additional
                <strong>compensation cess</strong> (e.g. certain luxury or sin
                goods), you should calculate the cess separately as per the
                notified rate and add it on top of the GST amount.
              </p>

              <h3>Is GST the same across all Indian states?</h3>
              <p>
                The <strong>GST rate structure</strong> is uniform across India,
                but the <strong>sharing</strong> of tax between Centre and
                States differs (CGST + SGST vs IGST). Some items may be exempt
                or taxed differently based on notifications, so always check the
                latest CBIC and State GST updates.
              </p>

